{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b2f3d4e5-0000-4000-8000-hospitalcrmcol",
    "name": "Hospital CRM — core-api",
    "description": "Local-dev collection for the hospital-crm core API.\n\nQuickstart:\n1. Import this collection + the environment file.\n2. Select the 'Hospital CRM — local' environment (top-right dropdown). NOTE: a collection-level fallback for baseUrl is included, so it also works without the environment selected.\n3. Run **Auth → Login — Doctor (Ada)** once; the post-response script stores the access/refresh tokens. Every other request inherits bearer auth automatically.\n\nPrescribe → dispense flow:\nLogin (Doctor) → Patients:List → Drugs:List → Encounters:List → Prescriptions:Create → Login (Pharmacist) → Dispensations:Create → Login (Admin) → Billing:List → Audit:List.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
